<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Microkernel&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://citeseer.csail.mit.edu/cs?q=microkernel" class="external text" title="http://citeseer.csail.mit.edu/cs?q=microkernel" rel="nofollow">scientific articles about microkernels</a> (on <a href="/wiki/CiteSeer" title="CiteSeer">CiteSeer</a>), including:
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFDan_Hildebrand1992">Dan Hildebrand (1992). "An Architectural Overview of QNX". <i>Proceedings of the Workshop on Micro-kernels and Other Kernel Architectures</i>: 113–126. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1880446421" class="internal">ISBN 1-880446-42-1</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=An+Architectural+Overview+of+QNX&amp;rft.jtitle=Proceedings+of+the+Workshop+on+Micro-kernels+and+Other+Kernel+Architectures&amp;rft.aulast=Dan+Hildebrand&amp;rft.au=Dan+Hildebrand&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.pages=113%E2%80%93126&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Microkernel"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> - the basic QNX reference.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFTanenbaum.2C_A..2C_Herder.2C_J._and_Bos.2C_H.2006">Tanenbaum, A., Herder, J. and Bos, H. (May 2006). "<a href="http://www.computer.org/portal/site/computer/menuitem.eb7d70008ce52e4b0ef1bd108bcd45f3/index.jsp?&amp;pName=computer_level1&amp;path=computer/homepage/0506&amp;file=cover1.xml&amp;xsl=article.xsl" class="external text" title="http://www.computer.org/portal/site/computer/menuitem.eb7d70008ce52e4b0ef1bd108bcd45f3/index.jsp?&amp;pName=computer_level1&amp;path=computer/homepage/0506&amp;file=cover1.xml&amp;xsl=article.xsl" rel="nofollow">Can We Make Operating Systems Reliable and Secure?</a>". <i>Computer</i> <b>39</b>: 44–51. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1109%2FMC.2006.156" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1109%2FMC.2006.156" rel="nofollow">10.1109/MC.2006.156</a></span><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.computer.org/portal/site/computer/menuitem.eb7d70008ce52e4b0ef1bd108bcd45f3/index.jsp?&amp;pName=computer_level1&amp;path=computer/homepage/0506&amp;file=cover1.xml&amp;xsl=article.xsl" class="external free" title="http://www.computer.org/portal/site/computer/menuitem.eb7d70008ce52e4b0ef1bd108bcd45f3/index.jsp?&amp;pName=computer_level1&amp;path=computer/homepage/0506&amp;file=cover1.xml&amp;xsl=article.xsl" rel="nofollow">http://www.computer.org/portal/site/computer/menuitem.eb7d70008ce52e4b0ef1bd108bcd45f3/index.jsp?&amp;pName=computer_level1&amp;path=computer/homepage/0506&amp;file=cover1.xml&amp;xsl=article.xsl</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Can+We+Make+Operating+Systems+Reliable+and+Secure%3F&amp;rft.jtitle=Computer&amp;rft.aulast=Tanenbaum%2C+A.%2C+Herder%2C+J.+and+Bos%2C+H.&amp;rft.au=Tanenbaum%2C+A.%2C+Herder%2C+J.+and+Bos%2C+H.&amp;rft.